elements.guidance:
A close relative is someone who you live in the same house with and is one of the following:
  • spouse
  • civil partner
  • partner who you've lived with for more than 2 years
  • a child under 18

elements.content: You must upload a digital document to show that you have the right to apply on behalf of the injured person.  This can include:
the full birth certificate showing both your and the injured person's names or
adoption certificate or
a care order or
a supervision order or
residence order or
other local authority order
What if any names have changed?
If any of the names on the documents have changed, upload evidence of this change. These can include:
marriage certificate
divorce certificate
change of name deed

elements.content: Make sure that:
your digital image shows the full document
the document is readable
the digital image of the document is on the device or computer you're using at the moment

sections.title: Application delay
sections.guidance: An application should be made within 2 years of the incident. If there are exceptional circumstances which meant an application couldn't have been made in that time, compensation could still be paid. </br> </br> There are other rules for injured persons who were under 18 at the time of the incident.

sections.title: Reporting details
sections.guidance: We can't make an award if the incident wasn't reported to the police.

elements.label: Was the incident reported to the police?
If the incident wasn't reported straight away, why was there a delay?
elements.guidance: We can't make an award unless the incident was reported to the police as soon as reasonably possible. We understand that certain incidents are difficult to report. That's why we'll consider the injured person's age, capacity and the effect the incident had on them if there was a delay.

elements.content: We want to make applying for compensation as easy as possible.
You've told us the injured person has scarring due to the incident. If this is their only injury, we have a service that allows us to settle their application quicker and without medical evidence.
If they choose this service, we'll:
check they are eligible
ask the police to send us a report of the crime
ask them to provide photographs of their scarring
write to them with a decision

elements.label: Do you want to use this service?

options.option: I want CICA to make a decision using only the police evidence and photos of my scarring.
I've suffered physical or disabling mental injuries. I want CICA to consider medical evidence before you make a decision.

sections.title: Victims of sexual assault: service options

elements.content: We want to make this application for compensation as easy as possible.  We pay compensation for crimes of sexual violence in recognition of the distress and mental trauma the injured person has suffered. We can use fixed payments based on the nature of the assault to settle their application quickly and with minimal intrusion.
If the injured person chooses this service we'll:
check their eligibility
ask the police to send us the crime report
not need to obtain and examine their medical records
make a decision on their application within 8 weeks, provided there are no police investigations that prevent the report being released
If we can't make a decision within 8 weeks we'll contact them to tell them why.
This service isn't appropriate for them if:
they have additional physical injuries or
they've suffered a disabling mental injury
These types of applications are more complex and take longer to decide as we need to examine their medical records or get a diagnosis from a psychiatrist or clinical psychologist.

elements.label: Please tell us how you want us to proceed

options.option: I want CICA to make a decision using only the police evidence.
I have suffered physical or disabling mental injuries. I want CICA to consider medical evidence before you make a decision.

sections.title: Treatment details
sections.guidance: We are asking about the injured person's treatment so we know the best time to get medical evidence.

elements.label: Has the injured person had any medical treatment for their injuries?
What's the name of the injured person's current GP or GP surgery?
elements.guidance: Even if the injured person hasn't seen their GP about their injuries we'll ask the GP for evidence to support this application.  GP records will include all information about the injured person's treatment, even if they only attended the hospital.

elements.content: What's the GP's address?

elements.label: When did they first receive treatment for their injuries?

sections.title: Medical evidence
sections.guidance: As part of our enquiries, we may ask the injured person to obtain medical evidence. </br> </br> They are responsible for obtaining this and paying up to 50 towards the cost. Depending on the injured person's circumstances we can pay this on their behalf but will deduct the cost from any compensation offered.

elements.label: Is the injured person able to take a request for medical evidence to their doctor for them to complete?
Tell us why they're unable to do this.
Can the injured person pay up to 50 of the cost of obtaining medical evidence to support their application?
elements.guidance:
We'll consider paying this charge if the injured person:
  • relies solely on any of these benefits
  • has a low income and is in receipt of certain tax credits
  • earns less than the minimum amount needed to qualify for Statutory Sick Pay
We'll recover the cost of this from any award we may make.

elements.label: Tell us why they're unable to pay for medical evidence.

sections.title: Medical information: psychological treatment
sections.guidance: For compensation to be paid for mental injuries, we need this to be confirmed by a clinical psychologist or psychiatrist.

elements.label: Has the injured person seen, or are they waiting to be seen by a clinical psychologist or psychiatrist?

sections.title: Previous applications
sections.guidance: We can only pay compensation for the same incident once.

elements.label: Has the injured person applied to us before for compensation for this incident?

sections.title: Compensation from other sources
sections.guidance: Other sources of compensation include social security benefits, insurance payments, civil damages and court compensation.

sections.title: Compensation from other sources
sections.guidance: We may not make a decision on this application until we're satisfied all reasonable steps have been taken to obtain other compensation which the applicant may be entitled to.
